==English==
'''Intelligent'''

=== Etymology ===
From Latin ''[[intelligens]]'', present participle of ''[[intelligere]]''

=== Adjective ===

# Of [[high]] or [[especial]]ly [[quick]] [[cognitive]] [[capacity]], [[bright]]
# Well thought-out, well considered (''an intelligent design'', ''an intelligent strategy'')
# Characterized by thoughtful interaction (''an intelligent conversation'').

